: habitational name from Ruhla in Thuringia."]}]},{"name":"Alan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Celtic origin and uncertain derivation (possibly a diminutive of a word meaning ‘rock’). It was introduced into England by  Breton  followers of  William the Conqueror , most notably  Alan , Earl of Brittany, who was rewarded for his services with vast estates in the newly conquered kingdom. In Britain the variants  <b>Allan</b>  and  <b>Allen</b>  are considerably less frequent, and generally represent transferred uses of surname forms, whereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alan Rule was born in 1185, in Roxburghshire, Scotland. He married Mrs Alan Rule before 1210, in Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1185–":"1185–Surnud","1187–Female":"1187–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","before 1210":"enne 1210","1210":"1210","1187":"1187","1185":"1185","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1185–":"1185–Kuollut","1187–Female":"1187–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1185–Male":"1185–Kuollut","before 1210":"ennen vuotta 1210","1210":"1210","1187":"1187","1185":"1185","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland","Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1185–":"1185–Décédé","1187–Female":"1187–Décédée","1210–Male":"1210–Décédé","1185–Male":"1185–Décédé","before 1210":"avant 1210","1210":"1210","1187":"1187","1185":"1185","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Scotland":"Écosse","Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Alan Rule est né en 1185, à Roxburghshire, Écosse. Il a épousé Mrs Alan Rule avant 1210, à Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au 